               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18260914-415-person2148">
                  SARAH 
                  BELLAMY
               <interp inst="t18260914-415-person2148" type="surname" value="BELLAMY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18260914-415-person2148" type="given" value="SARAH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18260914-415-person2148" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am the wife of John Bellamy; we live in <placeName id="t18260914-415-crimeloc2335">Gibralter-walk, Bethnal-green</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18260914-415-crimeloc2335" type="placeName" value="Gibralter-walk, Bethnal-green"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18260914-415-crimeloc2335" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18260914-415-off2334 t18260914-415-crimeloc2335"></join>. On Sunday, the 6th of August, at three o'clock, I went to the hospital to my husband, who had a broken leg - I left the prisoner, who is my lodger, in the yard; I left Susannah Hollinshead and some other persons in the house; there was no one in my apartments, which are the two lower rooms - the prisoner took his meals in our kitchen - the front window was fastened by two falling drops - and when I went out I fastened the door of my apartment - I returned about nine o'clock in the evening, and found the prisoner on the stairs, very much in liquor; he said he had lost the key of his door, and could not get into his room - I put him to a bed, in another room, where he slept all night - he went out the next morning - I received information, and went in search of him, and found him at a public-house, at the corner, pretty much in liquor - I asked where my two shillings were, which he had taken out of the drawer in my room - he said "Here it is, take it and bed d - d;" I had missed the two shillings from a screw-box in the drawer, and the rest of the property - we usually fasten my backwindow with a gimblet.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18260914-415-person2149">
                  GEORGE 
                  SMITH
               <interp inst="t18260914-415-person2149" type="surname" value="SMITH"></interp>
