                     <interp inst="t18260914-415-person2150" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a pawnbroker. I have a sheet and a remnant, pawned by the prisoner, early in the morning of the 7th of July; I gave the duplicates the witness has just produced.</p>
               <p>COURT to Mrs. BELLAMY. Q. Is this your sheet? A. Yes; it was safe during the absence of my husband; but I cannot say it was safe on the 6th of August - I had seen the money locked into the drawer that day - the drawer, where the sheet was, was not locked - he had lived with us fourteen or fifteen years - he had access to all our property - we had a good opinion of him.</p>
